  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Thursday, and Sophia announced this morning that she would inspect every bedroom in the house before dinner.",
      "zh": "星期四，Sophia 今天早上宣布，晚餐前她要檢查家裡每一間臥室。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She said a tidy room shows a tidy mind, which is a sentence she has said approximately one thousand times before.",
      "zh": "她說整齊的房間代表整齊的頭腦，這句話她大概已經講過一千次了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "My room has a bed, a desk, a small lamp, and one chair that is currently covered in clean clothes I have not put away.",
      "zh": "我房間裡有一張床、一張桌子、一盞小燈，還有一張目前堆滿還沒收好的乾淨衣服的椅子。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I quickly moved the clothes into a box and pushed the box into the corner, which is not exactly cleaning, but it works.",
      "zh": "我趕快把衣服搬進一個盒子，再把盒子推到角落，這不算是真的打掃，但確實有用。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William's room was a completely different story, and honestly, I am not sure the floor was visible at all.",
      "zh": "William 的房間完全是另一回事，老實說，我根本看不到地板在哪裡。"
    },
    {
      "en": "There were toys, a few empty boxes from his robot project, and one lonely sock sitting right in the middle of everything.",
      "zh": "裡面到處是玩具、幾個做機器人剩下的空盒子，還有一隻孤零零的襪子躺在正中央。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia stood in his doorway with her arms crossed and said, \"This room needs at least one hour of real work.\"",
      "zh": "Sophia 站在他房門口，雙手抱胸說：「這個房間至少需要一個小時的認真整理。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "William argued that a messy room is actually a sign of a very busy, very interesting mind, just like Sophia's tidy sentence, but backward.",
      "zh": "William 爭辯說亂七八糟的房間其實代表一顆很忙碌、很有趣的頭腦，就像 Sophia 那句話一樣，只是反過來。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia did not laugh at that joke even a little bit, and pointed at the door until he started cleaning.",
      "zh": "Sophia 完全沒被那個笑話逗笑，只是指著門口，直到他開始打掃為止。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I helped him for a while, mostly by sorting toys into one box and old homework papers into another.",
      "zh": "我幫了他一陣子，主要是把玩具分類進一個盒子，舊的作業紙分進另一個盒子。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Under his bed we found three missing socks, a broken pencil, and a photograph of our whole family from a few years ago.",
      "zh": "在他床底下我們找到三隻不見的襪子、一支斷掉的鉛筆，還有一張幾年前拍的全家福照片。"
    },
    {
      "en": "In the photo, William was still a baby, and I looked much shorter with a very strange haircut.",
      "zh": "照片裡 William 還是個嬰兒，而我看起來矮很多，還留著一個非常奇怪的髮型。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William laughed so hard at my old haircut that he had to sit down on his freshly cleaned floor.",
      "zh": "William 笑我以前的髮型笑到必須坐在他剛清乾淨的地板上。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I reminded him that in the same photo, he was wearing a bowl on his head like a hat, so he should not laugh too much.",
      "zh": "我提醒他，同一張照片裡他頭上還戴著一個碗當帽子，所以他也沒資格笑太大聲。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By the time Sophia came back to check, William's room had a clear floor, an empty desk, and a bed you could actually see.",
      "zh": "等 Sophia 再來檢查的時候，William 的房間已經地板淨空、桌子清空，連床都看得見了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She nodded once, said \"Better,\" and moved on to check the bathroom, which is a whole different kind of disaster.",
      "zh": "她點了一下頭，說了句「好一點了」，接著去檢查浴室，那又是另一種災難。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The bathroom mirror had toothpaste marks near the bottom, and there was a rubber duck sitting proudly on top of the sink.",
      "zh": "浴室的鏡子下方沾著牙膏漬，一隻橡皮鴨還很得意地坐在洗手台上。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William said the rubber duck was there to guard the toothbrushes, which I did not think needed guarding.",
      "zh": "William 說那隻橡皮鴨是負責守衛牙刷的，我倒覺得牙刷應該不需要什麼守衛。"
    },
    {
      "en": "After the inspection, Sophia sat down on the living room sofa and said the whole house finally felt calm again.",
      "zh": "檢查完之後，Sophia 坐在客廳沙發上，說整間房子終於又恢復平靜了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Perry immediately jumped up onto the same sofa and lay across her lap like he owned the whole room.",
      "zh": "Perry 馬上跳上同一張沙發，趴在她腿上，好像整個房間都是牠的一樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "So much for calm; but Sophia just smiled, patted his head, and let him stay right there.",
      "zh": "所以那個「平靜」也沒維持多久；不過 Sophia 只是笑了笑，拍拍牠的頭，就讓牠留在那裡了。"
    }
  ],
